text: Gustavsberg is a locality and the seat of Värmdö Municipality in Stockholm County, Sweden. In 2010, 11,333 people lived there. It is most known for its porcelain factory, Gustavsberg porcelain, and toilet bowls distributed nationwide and internationally. == References == == Other websites == * article Gustafsberg from Nordisk familjebok (1909) Category:Settlements in Stockholm County
